ratings.rComments: He's... okay. Honestly, I haven't learned anything. My friend has the other teacher, and she's actually learning things in ECON while I don't think I've learned much. You can use your notes for midterms and exams, sure, but I'd rather have been able to actually learn something. It just feels like he doesn't care.
Easy to pass, vivid lectures.

Basically show up and get the clicker points to get a B. The 3 exams are online so you can google all the answers. He has 12 quizzes on moodle. 2 are dropped. The final is in class and open note. I got a C+ which sucks, but I never went to class. So 'm very salty about how dumb I was. Don't be me. GO TO CLASS!

Super easy online quizzes. You take 3 midterms, all of which are also online. What makes this better is that out of the 3 midterms you take, only two are counted towards your grade. Final is open note, and is all repeat questions from past quizzes/tests. Super easy if you take the time to learn the basic concepts.
The easiest A I have ever gotten including high school courses.
Lots of free points if you show up to class. One midterm is dropped, and you can use your notes to help you on every test.

Easy A. You get unlimited tries on the weekly online quizzes. The midterms were all online. He let you take an answer bank into the final. I would recommend joining study room for the answer banks. Overall, very easy A.

Awesome teacher! He gives out so much extra credit. Midterms are online, as well as weekly quizzes, and prelectures. Final is open book/notes. If you have to take ECON, Vazquez is the only way to go. Attendance isn't mandatory, but you get extra credit by going and doing the I-Clickers.
This professor offers many chance for bonus points.
Easiest class ever. Show up to lecture for a whole bunch of extra credit.
too good to be true. 3 credit hour class, but study like you'd do for 1/2 credit hours. amazing lectures, amazing grades
It is an easy A.

If you're looking for an easy grade without learning a whole lot, take Vazquez.  I ended up with a solid A in his class, but can't tell you the basics of microeconomics.  His style of experimenting with teaching styles hinders the whole learning environment but he makes up for it with a LOT of extra credit and by giving relatively easy tests.
Class was really very easy and the lectures were interesting and clear. The prelectures were (mostly) great. If you show up you'll get an A.

Should be a pretty easy A. Online test are pretty easy and his lectures are ok. He gives out a ton of extra credit which is nice. The final is open note but he changed a lot of the questions this semester which is why grades are lower this semester.

Very easy and by far my favorite teacher. Weekly online homework assignments that you have multiple attempts on. 2 out of the three midterms were open booknote and they were exactly the same as the previous exams. The third midterm was online and you could easily find the answers. Lowest midterm dropped. Highly recommended if you like easy A's.
Vazquez makes lectures fun while still clearly going over the material from the prelectures .

Horrible instructor. Great entertainer. Lectures are treated as a game constantly meant to trick and not teach you.  No incentive to learn, given the easiness of the material. Too many people get grades not indicative of effort and knowledge of the subject. Class did little to add to what I learned in AP Macro.

Econ 102 is in a huge auditorium.  Uses iClicker questions as participation extra credit.  Very amusing in class, usually explains things well.  On occasion he has been misleading, but I only noticed because I had already learned what he meant from the online lectures before class.  I wish I could take another class with him.

Great professor! Made lectures comprehensible and enjoyable. Given material was so good and applicable that the textbook wasn't needed at all. Very understanding and helpful when you have issues too. Workload was fair.

Super easy teacher but feel that I only aced the class bc all the questions were basically the same with little variation. As far as real world application, I feel like I didn't learn much. You don't really need to go to class. Lectures were confusing to me, I relied mostly on the prelecture videos. Textbook is available, but I didn't buyread it.

OMG Jose is the best. He is the hottest teacher you will ever have in your life. His lecture is hilarious and he gives a lot of extra credits. Quiz and mid terms are all online, which is very easy. He is very nice guy... gosh I want to take ECON 102 again

This is the kind of professor that I look up to. As an electrical engineer, I took this as a Gen Ed, and I would take it again. I love this class, and I will remember it for the rest of my life. The class itself is very easy, discussion sections and lectures can be skipped, (although I would never skip the lectures). Easy A as well.
Vazquez is a fun and solid professor. Sometimes lecture can be a bit fast and I feel like he skims topics without enough depth, but he's popular with his students.

BEST PROFESSOR EVER! You technically don't need to go to his class to pass because it is all on line but I  found myself going anyways because he is so entertaining. Test are very easy and online so you can taking it with friends or google.

He's a very easy teacher that gives out a lot of extra credit.  Also, the tests are online and the final is open-note and open-book.  His lectures are great, though, to be honest.  He is very entertaining, too.
Vazquez is awesome. Gives out a lot of credit and class is easy.

Lectures are interesting, must go to them bc use of iclicker points. Online quizes that you can retake multiple times to get full points. Tests arent too difficult. Would recommend if looking for a class without alot of work.

JOSE IS THE BEST. Seriously take this class with him it will be the best decision you ever make for your career at UIUC. He's amazing. All exams are online except for the final, but the final is open book, notes. You get to drop your lowest midterm grade as well. Weekly quizzes & prelectures but he drops a lot of them. And he's big on extra credit.

Joseee!!! He's the best professor ever, he canceled classes frequently but that didn't even matter since he made his classes fun. Barely use the book, drops a exam, drops quizzes and pre lectures. hes basically giving you a A. all the exams are online as well.
super funny, he brought his dogs to explain concepts of economics. He's a cool guy

best thing you can do for yourself as a student at u of i is taking econ with him. not only is his class ridiculously easy, but all the other econ teachers are very boring and their classes are hard. everything is online, lots of extra credit, no papers
Easiest class ever. gives out a lot of extra credit, quizzes and exams are open notes. Jose is funny and an interesting teacher.

Vazquez was one of the easiest profs ever. He makes lecture interesting and gets the students' attention. His accent was hard to understand at first but it got easier with time. The exams were really easy and were taken straight from the weekly quizzes. The only time I ever used the textbook was on the final. He also gives a lot of extra credit.

By far the best professor I have had so far. Very interesting and engaging, knows how to keep the attention of close to 600 students in a lecture hall. The exams were easy but still taught me a lot of skills. One of U of I's biggest assets for economics/finance/business.
Very funny and entertaining man, but very confusing. Has trouble explaining the material where it can be understood. You basically have to teach yourself, which makes the class seem pointless.

The class is quite easy. You will have weekly online quizzes, pre-lecture quiz to take (only 4 questions at most).  Attendance is not mandatory, but he always has iclicker questions.  He offers a lot of extra credit.  Vazquez is a very funny guy and makes the class interesting.  Explains course material clearly, and make the course enjoyable.

This guy is the bomb! From giving extra credit for ppl going on dates to bringing his dogs in to class, Jose Vazquez has definitely converted a subject that could otherwise be extremely tedious and boring into the most fun class of this semester for me :D
awesome

Very easy class. Lecture not required, but very interactive and lots of extra credit opportunities. 3 exams all open note, internet, book, etc. Weekly quizzes that can be taken until 100% is earned. Basically impossible not to get a good grade. Discussion section is somewhat helpful.
Easy course for almost every one. And Jose's is fun
He is one of the best in the university. Although my major is CS, I start loving Econ because of him.
he is cool
great techniques
His lectures are very entertaining and enjoyable. Best lecturer I've had so far by a long shot. He makes good use of IClickers to his audience of several hundred students engaged.

While Jose was an interesting and funny guy, his lectures were often confusing, despite the generally easy concepts. He kept his TAs uninformed, and overall the class was sloppily put together. Luckily, all three of the midterms are online, and there is no reason why someone shouldn't get a good grade in this class. If you want an easy A, take him.

He does not teach in his lectures. He just gives questions for i-clicker extra credits during lectures. His midterms were online, which are pretty much all found online. There are weekly quizzes. The final was word for word from the midterms. Just teach yourself by reading the book and practice the quizzes before exams.

Worst. teacher. ever. he explains nothing, and gives awful examples that i cant understand. iclicker questions in class are usually much simpler than quiz questions. you get to the quiz and wonder when you discussed any of it in class. basically ,you teach yourself if you dont want to fail. i also have trouble understanding his accent.

Literally, the most confusing teacher/professor I've ever had. He "knows" economics, but has no idea how to explain it to anyone. His clickers/quizzes/exams are so contradictory and usually have more than 1 right answer, but you're supposed to choose the "most correct" answer. I barely learned anything and regret having him "teach" me.

i would not advise taking econ with him. going to class is pointless since he explains nothing. his i clicker questions are easy but the quizzes are so much more difficult. i have gained nothing from taking econ with vazquez.
It's extremely easy and even don't have to pay attention. Just do all the practice questions posted on the website before the exam and you will get an A. And he is soooooooooo charming!

His lectures are interesting and his test questions are the practice questions that he posts online word-for-word. Even the final is comprised of practice questions and old midterm questions AND you even get extra credit for attending lecture! I'd highly recommend taking his class.

It's like the easiest class ever and he literally throws extra credit at you. Don't even have to go to class unless you like extra credit and then you don't even have to pay attention. He even drops your lowest test grade.
Good professor. Too cool for school. Isn't too clear but has amazing teaching techniques.

I really liked Vasquez until I took the final.  I was doing well in his class and enjoyed his lectures, he made them interesting and applicable.  However, a lot of people, including myself, failed the final after doing well on the tests all semester.  I felt that it was totally unexpected and unfair which is why I'm no longer a fan.

One of the best Econ profs at U of I. He uses good examples and makes the class more interesting. If u go through the practice questions the midterms are easy and u r allowed to bring a cheat sheet. But the final was ridiculously hard
He is nice and helpful, but his class is extremely hard!!! Half the class failed the first midterm and he doesn't curve at all! Don't take him if you want an A or B in the class!!!

The class was pretty easy, but pretty much everyone got a D or failed the final. He wouldn't respond to students on Compass who were complaining that there was a fundamental problem with it; no one did well on it. His questions all throughout the semester were ambiguous and just odd in general. And your fate in the class depended on those questions

This class was very stressful. They must have screwed up the scantron arrangement or something. I like economics a lot and I worked hard on studying, and I left the exams feeling confident, and then I'd get my grade and I'd have a 60% or something. On one exam I got 13/25 when they returned with my grade. I do not trust Vazquez or his TAs' exams.

I believe that the test for the final had a fundamental problem and professor refused to address this. By not responding to emails, this def put heavy burdens on the students. I also cannot emphasize on the deceptive word of "extra credit". Do not trust that word. I assure you; it will not help you out much. Do well on tests!!!!
Lectures were boring. Just attended them for Bonus points. Exams were easy. Easy class
Easy and interesting class, easy midterm, but hard final.
Def. an easy A class. Tons of extra credit. Best economics class I have ever taken.
Gives out a lot of extra credit. The final was ridiculously hard but ended up with an A. Definitely the best ECON professor here hands down.

Very easy teacher. He makes lectures interesting with plenty of relevant examples. Test are made from questions from the homework and the lectures, so they are all problems that you have done before. He lets you use cheat sheets on all the tests, so put example problems on the Cheat sheet! he also drops the lowest midterm and homework assignment.

Jose uses examples that make class more interesting and are more relevant to our age group. He gives you tons of practice questions before exams, and cheat sheets. The questions on the exams are always the practice questions, so just put the practice Qs on your cheat sheet! If you have to take Econ 102, i would DEFINITELY recommend Jose!!

Jose makes the class really easy with lots of extra credit. You get to use a cheat sheet for each of the 3 exams (and 3 cheat sheets for the final). Lowest midterm is dropped. But, the final is considerably more difficult than the other exams and practice questions. You really need to know the material for the final! (Fall 2011)
easy a class. great professor, offers a lot of extra credit and you get to use cheat sheets on the exams! and he drops the lowest exam grade. makes econ an interesting subject. jose is awesome!

By far the easiest 302 professor.  This class was way easier than 102 and 103.  He basically gives you the answers on the tests on compass and the homeworks are very simple.  You  drop your lowest test.  Also a lot of extra credit.  This really should not be a 300 level class.  Try to get him as the other 302 classes are notoriously difficult.
Good teacher. Gives a lot of extra credit opportunities
i love him soooo much. I have never saw such a charming professor. He explains everything well, and he is so hot. I really want to be his TA when i were a mater of econ.

Jose goes above and beyond to make sure his students succeed. He offers extra credit and makes sure that everything you need to be successful on exams can be found online. He is a quality professor. I highly recommend him.

Jose is one of the best Econ professors that I have had. He makes lecture fun. I have NEVER fallen asleep in class.He always stay after class and after office hours to help answer questions. It's almost impossible to not get an A with all of the extra credits, drop lowest test score, straight-forward exams.I highly recommend him!

Jose is the man. He keeps a subject that many find dull quite entertaining. The lectures are based off the text, but are much more conceptual than fact based. He provides a real world perspective on a very theoretical subject. HE IS AWESOME!
Awesome teacher.  The class is pretty much a joke but he teaches you the material in a way that is really easy to understand.  All of these negative posts are wrong.

He was an okay lecturer but never responded to emails and basically refused to have any contact with students outside of class. He also forgot to submit our grades at the end of the semester, giving everyone a NR for the course and repeatedly blamed issues on "the grader" instead of taking responsibility for his own mistakes.

After forcing the entire class to read the syllabus and take a quiz on it to make sure we understood, he completely disregarded the syllabus and ignored the grading policies it outlined.  He doesn't realize that pop quizzes don't make sense in an online setting.  Weekly homework was long, and some questions were verbatim repeats of others.  Avoid!
Doesn't know what he's talking about, makes easy calculations seem like 500 level math theory.  Tests are confusing as hell and lecture is pointless.  Take it at a community college.

Pretty easy course. A lot of online homework, 3 tests where cheat sheets are allowed, and a little extra credit offered throughout the semester. The extra credit wasn't really worth it based on the amount of work put into it, but it's good that it's there. I didn't go to lecture the majority of the semester and I still did well in the class.
Has to be the easiest professor for this class. four 6 question tests that you get a cheat sheet with anything you want on it. If you can take it with him absolutely do
Jose is not a bad professor...he's just a terrible test maker. It all seems relatively easy until you get his tests which were ambiguous as hell and you don't feel at all prepared for them.

He keeps the class interesting, the homework relates to the lecture material, but his tests were totally off. They were worded weirdly and were confusing. Even though I studied, I didn't do well on the tests, which messed up my grade.
Definitely a fun class and need to attend to get the 2 bonus points + bonus points on the exam. Wait for this guy to teach before taking gotheil.
BEST ECON 102 Professor at U of I. Gets straight to the point in class material. Keeps students engaged. Jose is a genius.
Awesome professor. lots of bonus questions. you should definitely wait until you can get a class with him. goes circles around gohteil.

This course is easy and I think Jose is trying pretty hard to keep the students' interest. So I give him props. He basically provided everything[cheat sheet,taped lectures,previous exams,extra credit] you need to get an A, sadly people failed to take full advantage. He dresses well..but it doesn't suite his age.

I don't see why everyone is saying the material he teach in class is unrelated to microeconomics. He cut straight to the point. His tests are easy too. Anyway previous exams are the best material, read over textbook, and go over the clicker questions and you'll ace the course.
Tests were ridiculously hard compared to lecture material.  Several of the questions had grammar errors as well which led to ambiguity.
His tests did not seem to have to do with what he was teaching and some of the questions were ambiguous due to the way they were worded.

Vazquez seems like a pretty good guy and he dresses like a model, but his test have almost nothing to do with lecture.  And the information in the lectures don't really allow you to truly comprehend economic principles; you have to use your book for that.  Also, the test are way to hard for the material presented.

This class SHOULD be easy, but sadly it's a Gen Ed that's harder than it should be. The material is easy enough, but Vasquez' tests are ridiculously ambiguous, so you never know what he's really getting at. His lectures are pointless except for the occasional iClicker extra credit and he also seems to get crap TAs. Just read the book and good luck!

Jose is the man. His keen fashion sense and stylish jeans make coming to class a must. He claims that he isn't trying to "trick" you on the tests but his exam questions are always tougher than his example questions. Beware of hard tests.

Lectures are pretty pointless with examples pertaining to sex, drugs, or alcohol. Makes simple concepts confusing. However, if you have background knowledge in econ, this class should be a breeze for you. Get cheat sheets on tests and extra credit points from iClicker and labs.
tricky exam...

Jose is amazing! What a great guy! He is hilarious, cool, and HOT.  He is hard to understand at first because of his accent, but you will get used to it. He is much better than Gottheil.  If you have the choice between the two, take Jose all day :)

Really easy. Drops the lowest midterm. But lectures are just short of useless. They mostly contain pointless examples relating to parties/alcohol/sex. He thinks it helps keep college students attentive but it doesn't. Just reading the relevant chapters properly before the exam guarantees a good grade. Exams contain a lot of Aplia questions.

Ugh. This man is the most useless prof ever. I knew the material going in, but if anything he made it more confusing. He complicates the most basic material with irrelevant examples. probably better than gotheil though..

Easiest econ teacher ever. He doesn't teach much though. But If his exams were any easier, it'd be unfair. You get a cheat sheet and he drops 1 exam grade. Gives extra credit with iclickers/labs, so theres an incentive to attend class. I never went, but read a little from the book to do the online homework. If you have common sense you'll get an A.

Irresponsible and Incompetent Economics Professor who doesn?t teach very well (Agreed Fact). He uses the same PPP deck that he used 4 semesters ago, and he does not change the ERRORS in them. Once said, "Last semester nobody found this error" (thinks its funny) People like him because he lets the class use Cheat Sheets and drops your lowest exam.

I found this class to be more difficult than I expected. His lectures, while fairly engaging,  don't really do a good job of covering the material on the exams. The fact that one of the three major exam scores is dropped makes this class fairly easy, but don't go in expecting a cakewalk just because he isn't Gottheil.

i'm not a big fan. i took econ before, so i knew the concepts but when he would explain i would just end up confused. he likes to do examples and stuff BEFORE teaching the concept, which isnt helpful. he likes to walk around FA as he talks, which is distracting. but good news you get cheat sheets, tests all mc, drop lowest exam, and no book!

Everything you learn is common sense. Many concepts arent even covered in class and often the concepts are just alluded to and arent directly engaged. After the first few weeks I stopped going to class, wound up with an A+. In terms of covering the material, easily the worst prof Ive had. That being said, the class is really easy.

He is awful.  Tries to make things "cool" and "interesting", but you just end up missing the point.. I wouldn't recommend this for Econ majors because you're actually going to need to know the material later.  For all else, it's ok if you don't need to retain anything from this class.

You get a cheat sheet on exams and your lowest grade is dropped, but that didn't make the class easy for me.  Exams are pretty vague.  I wasn't really a fan and didn't learn much, but I'd still take Vasquez over Gottheil when it comes to micro econ.
He sucks. The guy cant even speak or write in proper english and the tests are nothing like the homework or classwork.  This was by far the most disappointing class I've taken at the university.

GREAT GUY!!  The class was really hard and confusing (bcus i don't understand econ). But if you went in for help he made things REALLY clear!  Our class had 3 take home exams and a TAKE HOME final!  No work except for like 2 really busy weeks at the end and a term paper. REALLY nice HOT guy! amazing dresser too.
I'm sure he knows his econ well, but is overall not a smart person. He certainly enjoys being himself. It's an easy class to take if it's required.

202's similar to his 102. There are 3 midterms, one of which is dropped. Online hw, clickers. and a final. In fall 06, he basically made every waste $ on a crappy clicker (not an i-clicker). We were pretty angry. Go to the discussion for further help. Jose's exams have a lot of variance. Some are really easy, some are pretty hard.

This guy is a great teacher.  He tells you exactly what you need to know for the exam.  GREAT TEACHER!  Sometimes, you will have to make an effort and study because some of the stuff may be fuzzy like a panda.  BESIDES THAT HE IS HILARIOUS!!!! HE DRESSES LIKE HE IS GOING CLUBBING!!  MY FRIENDS ALWAYS LAUGHED AT THAT!!  SILLY JOSE!

What can I say? Jose is just that dude. His class is enjoyable and he is very fair. He lets you drop your lowest test score and his tests are not that bad. Reccomend him for any econ class. Much easier than everyone else.

He is just awesome.  If you took any kind of stats in HS you'll do just fine.  He's so laid back and you get out of class early almost every lecture. Accent = TOTALLY HOT! If only his teaching skills were as good as his fashion sense...

Jose's a good professor, but he has the privilege of having some great TA's. Harry Tsang and Micah Pollak are great teaching assistants, and if you have either of them, you are very lucky. Jose has a great option of dropping your lowest midterm grade (out of three exams) which is good in case you have a bad night or anything like that. Good luck!

he was very unapproachable. when i got sick and spent part of the day in the hospital and missed an exam b/c i had a 102.3 temp, he refused to let me make it up although i had a doctor's note. i felt like i was being treated unfairly, almost as if i was being punished for getting sick. i was very upset over this.

Fundamentally one of the easiest teachers you will ever have - however he doesn't teach very well. Lets you use cheat sheets on exams and gives extra credit if you attend lecture. The problem is he asks VERY ambiguous questions on the exams. I would still pick him over any other teacher though.
Alright teacher, however we're 5 weeks behind. Lets you use cheat sheets on all exams, and drops the lowest exam grade - the material he teaches is extremely ambiguous though.
Great Professor. Keeps dry material interesting.
SexY :-)

Great professor, very helpful. The class is weighted very heavily, but its easy to get a B or A. If you show up to class and do the labs you automatically get extra credit, and class is usually pretty funny.

This guy is great. Don't need the book. His lectures have tons of mistakes but with all drug and beer examples this is the only class i went to during the semester. The dude is simply a baller. Oh and supposedly he's my father-in-law.

Pretty easy class.  Basic stats are learned, nothing really too tricky.  He moves slowly so it's easy to keep up.  First exam was extremely easy, 2nd pretty tough, 3rd alright.  Cumulative Final, HW is online, not too bad.

First off, I never used the book. I would advise you to just borrow one, if ever needed. I have Vazquez again for 202. His exam questions are quite vague. I feel like I sufficiently argue that multiple answers are right depending on how you read the question. My TA was terrible so I never went to discussion.If you have a good TA, they help with HW.

Don't know if he still teaches this section. I took all his lecture notes and helpful examples for granted and ended up with a B in the class -- if I hadn't, I would have had an A. He is really organized and will take the time to sit down with you. Recommended! 302 is hard in general, don't know about his teaching in that class.
I enjoyed his class, though it was pretty difficult. Lowest grade I've received at U of I.

Wow.. where do you even begin. Honestly, out of my past 3 years at U of I, "Jose" is by far the worst professor I ever had. He has so many mistakes and errors on his homeworks, exams and everything in between it's unreal that he is still employed at the University. His tests are ambiguous, his grading style is ridiculous, and he has wasted my life.
Much harder class than I thought it would be because his tests are ambigious. He is a good teacher but wierd grader.
Awesome professor!

I agree with the comment below mine, students should understand material before the test, not after he answers thier questions regarding the test.  He also has a very unclear grading system that make it impossible to accurately gauge your progress in the class.  He tries very hard to make econ intersting, but he still fails as an effective teacher.

The tests are extremely ambiguous and questions sometimes deal with the craziest topics I've ever heard discussed in economics! Sure, he explains things well, AFTER the test is done and people bombard with questions due to his lack of ability to create a clear and straightforward test! Many people seem to be orgasming over his dress, but who cares?

Highly recommended.  Econ 302 is supposed to be an extremely difficult class, and it is.  But if you take it with Vazquez, you'll feel a lot better.  Much better to take it with him than any other professor.  He's a fun guy and you'll really enjoy him.

Vasquez wants people to do well.  The first exam is overwhelming (50% mean) because it is unlike anything you've ever taken. Text not necessary. Attend lecture, he often takes attendance through turning in class labs.  2nd and 3rd exams he allows cheat sheets, very similar format to 1st exam. Study by doing homework and lab questions several times.

Great professor, was clever in the way he taught. Put many of the economic topics into perspective with great examples. His tests aren't the easiest, but I learned a lot in his class, I really recommend him.
This teacher was horrible, his accent got in the way of my learning and he was just too difficult to learn from.  My TA spoke like she just got off the boat from China.
Prof. Vazquez keeps lectures interesting, and I've learned a lot this semester.
He is interesting to listen to in class, though sometimes his accent can get in the way.

I hated him at the beginning of the class because it seemed like he was not explaining the things that were on the test. It is a very differnt way of thinking about economics. His first test will be a shock, but once you realize how he wants you to think. THe material is pretty easy. 3 tests, no quizzes, and easy online HW's

I already took 2 classes that he teaches and am taking the another one next semester. He is definitely easier then the other professors though at times I feel I'm not learning what I need to learn. Class is very organized. He makes millions of mistakes on his powerpoints.
Good and fair prof.

His beautiful accent made paying attention in my 8am with Professor Jose Vazquez no problem.  He was very helpful and a great dresser, not to mention the fact that he's somewhat young and with it!  I went to his office to discuss a paper and he was burning incense.

He is a funny guy. He explains things very well and his tests are relatively easy (no suprises- you know what will be on the test). Such a snazzy dresser- i'm sure if I paid as much attention to the lecture as I did his appearance I would have done better.
He's got that fire, what else can you say.  Plus, he's good with numbers.  You wanna know what your chances are with him.... he could probably calculate them for you.
Jose is amazing!  He is very clear, very concise, and there will never be surprises on the exams.  Don't take econ with any other professors if you have a chance to take it with Jose!
Great Professor. There are no supprises on the exams, especially if you go to review sessions and are in class before taking the exams.

I love Jose, and you will too. I think he actually might be associated with 202 next semester, but definitely give him a try. If his dressing doens't impress you enough, then maybe his teaching will! :)

As everyone else said, he did dress rather well! For someone who had to take the class for a gen. ed., but hates numbers/econ, this was a great class. He explains things really well and grades fairly. If you can get Harry Tsang as your TA, he's really helpful (and a little crazy).

Omg i love this guy Vasquez, one of the best professor in this univerity, he goes very easy on the exams, and the overall course is fairly student friendly so u won't be stressed out, highly recommended

This is the guy you want to take. Much easier than Schultz.  You want to get in good with your TA becuase he might help your grade out in the end if your TA thinks you were deserving. Take Wen for a TA if you can. She rocks!

Jose is such an amazing guy! He's very skilled at economics! He's also pretty hunky! He dresses so nicely... I wish every guy dressed like him. And he's really easy to approach and talk to. He'll explain anything, and he gets back to every email he receives.
I've never actually gone to office hours or anything for him, but from lecture he's pretty clear.  Plus he's a snazzy dresser and man that accent whew.  Sorry I might need a moment.

Vazquez was a nice guy, but his class is completely unorganized.  He used another teachers slides, and then posted different ones online.  He was all over the place and exams tested concepts that we never covered in class.  He made the class much more complicated than it should have been.
Great teacher. Explains everything clearly. A tremendous imporvement on Baer or Gothiel. Has a great accent too. Dresses so sharply!

Though the class itself is difficult, Professor Vazquez really tries to make it more understandable. He is always willing to help and involves students in class discussion. I would recommend him if you have to take this course.
